	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />It depends on which games, and what mappers they use. I made a multicart of <em>The Legend of Zelda</em> and three NROM games by using the MMC1 mapper with <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/ForbiddenFour.7z" class="postlink">my own menu code</a>.
<br />
<br />But by far, the easiest way to make a multicart is to take the PocketNES engine and release on Game Boy Advance. Jaleco is one of the companies that did this commercially.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


